{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/10157", "repo": "rails", "body": "@fxn You are right. But those chdir calls are required because `find_executable_in_parent_path` doesn't return the full path of executable. It just returns `script/rails` or `bin/rails`.\r\n\r\nBut here it returns full path to executable so we can directly do `exec RUBY, exe, *ARGV` instead of again checking for `cwd == Dir.pwd` and recursing.\r\n\r\nInfact, we can drop cwd as it will not be used now.", "_id": {"$oid": "523cf300bd354364b900372d"}, "issue_id": 10157, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/16160124", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10157#issuecomment-16160124", "updated_at": "2013-04-10T07:50:57Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/prathamesh-sonpatki/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/prathamesh-sonpatki/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/prathamesh-sonpatki/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/prathamesh-sonpatki/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/prathamesh-sonpatki", "login": "prathamesh-sonpatki", "gravatar_id": "1b0973b64704738dbc8ce24d8382bb1f", "html_url": "https://github.com/prathamesh-sonpatki", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/prathamesh-sonpatki/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/prathamesh-sonpatki/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/prathamesh-sonpatki/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/1b0973b64704738dbc8ce24d8382bb1f?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F10a7864f54092aa82b4a41d2f0ec370c.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/prathamesh-sonpatki/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 621238, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/prathamesh-sonpatki/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2013-04-10T07:50:57Z", "id": 16160124, "owner": "rails"}
